number tomorrow.

23:03.605 --> 23:05.204
- You're getting a new number?
- There he is!

23:05.206 --> 23:06.272
Rhi! That's not
Steve's cousin!

23:06.274 --> 23:07.373
I don't even think he's gay!

23:07.375 --> 23:08.909
- What?
- I'm sorry, I have to go.

23:08.911 --> 23:10.442
- I'll explain later. Promise.
- What?

23:10.444 --> 23:11.979
Where are you going?

23:11.981 --> 23:12.982
Go, go, go!

23:15.783 --> 23:17.416
Oh, hell no!

23:17.418 --> 23:18.584
Wait, you guys!

23:18.586 --> 23:19.787
Come on, come on!

23:19.789 --> 23:21.089
Leave him alone!

23:22.156 --> 23:23.655
Don't creep on our women,
little dude!

23:23.657 --> 23:24.859
Rhi, give me my keys!

23:25.924 --> 23:26.970
No, Justin, you can't!

23:26.994 --> 23:28.461
- Justin!
- My keys!

23:28.463 --> 23:30.463
No,
you cannot drive right now.

23:30.465 --> 23:32.167
Who even was that?

23:53.021 --> 23:55.657
Siri. Hey, Siri!

23:56.492 --> 23:58.157
Do I have a phone?

23:58.159 --> 24:00.862
<i>It is 6:29 a.m.</i>

24:17.378 --> 24:19.645
<i>This teenager missed curfew,</i>

24:19.647 --> 24:22.048
<i>then said the Devil
made him do it.</i>

24:22.050 --> 24:24.217
<i>Monroeville's Nathan Daldry,
was found</i>

24:24.219 --> 24:26.486
<i>asleep around 1:00,
Saturday morning,</i>

24:26.488 --> 24:29.622
<i>by the side of a highway
with a broken back windshield.</i>

24:29.624 --> 24:31.191
<i>His explanation...</i>

24:31.193 --> 24:32.625
<i>He had been
possessed by Satan.</i>

24:32.627 --> 24:33.894
Your boy took down
his social media.

24:33.896 --> 24:34.994
<i>So tell us what happened.</i>

24:34.996 --> 24:36.061
Guess I gotta
talk to him in person.

24:36.063 --> 24:38.263
Justin, what are you thinking?

24:38.265 --> 24:39.798
Leave him alone.
He's disturbed.

24:39.800 --> 24:42.070
Then why were you even
hanging out with him?

24:43.338 --> 24:44.737
I don't know.

24:44.739 --> 24:46.019
<i>And one day,
I was fine.</i>

24:47.076 --> 24:49.910
So, Friday night
he was super weird.

24:49.912 --> 24:51.010
And then, this morning,

24:51.012 --> 24:52.814
I get a text from
a random number.

24:53.848 --> 24:54.914
"If you meet me in person,

24:54.916 --> 24:57.182
somewhere public,
I can explain.

24:57.184 --> 24:58.718
Please come alone."

24:58.720 --> 25:00.287
Oh, my God. Are you going to?

25:00.289 --> 25:02.188
I don't know, should I?

25:02.190 --> 25:03.390
I think you have to.

25:03.392 --> 25:04.490
This is the coolest,
creepiest thing

25:04.492 --> 25:06.060
that has ever happened.

25:34.990 --> 25:36.692
Tell me you're alone.
You're alone, right?

25:37.892 --> 25:39.925
I'm sorry, do I know you?

25:39.927 --> 25:41.629
Oh, Nathan sent me.

25:43.698 --> 25:44.899
Oh, um...

25:45.434 --> 25:47.532
Where is Nathan?

25:47.534 --> 25:49.134
He's here.

25:49.136 --> 25:51.336
In a way. I mean, he's not,
like, "here" here,

25:51.338 --> 25:53.006
but he also wasn't there
on Friday when you met him.

25:53.008 --> 25:54.443
Or you thought
that you met him.

25:55.444 --> 25:56.744
You know, you actually didn't.

25:57.178 --> 25:58.413
What?

25:59.013 --> 26:00.946
Today I'm Megan.

26:00.948 --> 26:04.150
The day that you met Nathan,
I was Nathan. All right?

26:04.152 --> 26:06.486
And the day that Amy shadowed
you at school, I was Amy.

26:06.488 --> 26:09.158
And the day that you went
to the beach with Justin...

26:10.291 --> 26:11.827
I was Justin.

26:12.927 --> 26:15.894
Because I am someone
who wakes up

26:15.896 --> 26:17.599
in a different body every day.

26:19.734 --> 26:23.036
Always someone my age.
Never too far from the last,

26:23.038 --> 26:25.838
never the same person twice,

26:25.840 --> 26:29.509
and I have absolutely
no control over any of it.

26:29.511 --> 26:32.011
Okay, did Rebecca
tell you I'd be here?

26:32.013 --> 26:33.945
She wasn't supposed
to tell anyone.

26:33.947 --> 26:35.915
I don't know why it happens,
I don't know how.

26:35.917 --> 26:37.083
I mean, this is...

26:37.085 --> 26:38.317
No one's ever tried
to explain it to me.

26:38.319 --> 26:40.452
And this is the first time
I've ever actually

26:40.454 --> 26:41.756
told anyone about it.

26:43.625 --> 26:45.761
And I know
I'm not doing a good job.

26:49.364 --> 26:51.333
Okay. Um...

26:52.767 --> 26:57.336
Thank you.
This is all very good,

26:57.338 --> 26:59.174
but I think I should go.

27:01.976 --> 27:03.776
"You have a nice smile."

27:03.778 --> 27:06.112
That was the fortune
that you got.

27:06.114 --> 27:08.214
The fortune that we both got.

27:08.216 --> 27:10.048
You told me about the day
that your dad got laid off.

27:10.050 --> 27:11.317
You told me about
the French restaurant.

27:11.319 --> 27:12.952
Okay, just stop.

27:12.954 --> 27:14.887
I told Justin those things,
not you.

27:14.889 --> 27:17.057
He has nothing
to do with this.

27:17.059 --> 27:18.824
He's the only one who does.

27:18.826 --> 27:20.692
I spent the day with him.

27:20.694 --> 27:24.230
And now he and you and Nathan,
and God knows who else

27:24.232 --> 27:25.565
are playing some stupid joke.

27:25.567 --> 27:28.067
And, honestly,
I don't even want to know why.

27:28.069 --> 27:29.402
So just, please, stop.

27:29.404 --> 27:31.440
He doesn't talk to you
like this.

27:32.540 --> 27:34.039
He doesn't spend days with you

27:34.041 --> 27:35.601
like the one that
we had together, okay?

27:36.544 --> 27:38.046
He doesn't see you.

27:43.018 --> 27:46.722
You have to know
that that wasn't him.

27:50.091 --> 27:51.694
It's not possible.

27:52.360 --> 27:53.462
It is.

28:08.643 --> 28:10.276
Hey.

28:10.278 --> 28:11.845
Hey! I'm all right.

28:11.847 --> 28:14.383
I seem not all right to you?
I'm fine.

28:15.050 --> 28:16.649
Great.

28:16.651 --> 28:19.951
Do you wanna study at my place
after school?

28:19.953 --> 28:21.757
- "Study."
- Who's Megan?

28:22.723 --> 28:23.759
I don't know any Megan.

28:24.492 --> 28:26.660
Did you tell anyone

28:26.662 --> 28:29.865
about what I told you about
what happened with my dad?

28:30.299 --> 28:31.730
Um...

28:31.732 --> 28:33.231
Honestly, I don't
even remember

28:33.233 --> 28:35.436
what you told me
about your dad.

28:45.413 --> 28:48.584
What's wrong with you?
Are we hanging out or what?

28:52.588 --> 28:53.922
Whatever.

29:21.950 --> 29:24.349
Hey! It's me, A.

29:24.351 --> 29:25.719
Oh.

29:25.721 --> 29:26.722
Hi. Um...

29:29.491 --> 29:30.655
Wait, "A"?

29:30.657 --> 29:33.026
He's James, but I'm A.

29:33.028 --> 29:36.829
Like, just A, like the letter.

29:36.831 --> 29:39.635
I'm still not convinced
that this is real.

29:41.703 --> 29:43.836
Who named you A?

29:43.838 --> 29:48.674
I did. I wanted a name that no
one else was likely to have.

29:48.676 --> 29:51.711
Okay, the day you were Justin,
what was I wearing?

29:51.713 --> 29:54.049
Peasant blouse, jean shorts.

29:55.384 --> 29:56.548
What?

29:56.550 --> 29:58.217
You know what
a peasant blouse is?

29:58.219 --> 30:00.385
Half the time
I wake up as a girl.

30:00.387 --> 30:02.455
Although, I will say,
I think that James

30:02.457 --> 30:04.758
could totally pull it off.
I think...

30:04.760 --> 30:06.759
Got the physique for it,
all that good stuff.

30:06.761 --> 30:07.995
Okay.

30:10.065 --> 30:12.499
What was the last thing
I said to you that day?

30:12.501 --> 30:13.865
"Your mouth tastes
so much better

30:13.867 --> 30:14.933
when you don't smoke."

30:14.935 --> 30:16.035
And the name
you called Justin

30:16.037 --> 30:17.770
to his face when
you were Nathan?

30:17.772 --> 30:20.041
What? Oh, Galahad.

30:20.742 --> 30:21.840
And when you were Amy,

30:21.842 --> 30:23.308
who showed you around
after I did?

30:23.310 --> 30:24.545
Alexander.

30:27.382 --> 30:29.147
You still could be a liar.

30:29.149 --> 30:31.384
Just a ridiculously
well-prepared liar.

30:31.386 --> 30:33.086
Or I could be
telling you the truth.

30:33.088 --> 30:35.188
Or I could be going insane.

30:35.190 --> 30:37.890
Who are you?
Who are your parents?

30:37.892 --> 30:39.895
Do they switch
bodies every day?

30:40.895 --> 30:42.028
Hey, do you mind if we go

30:42.030 --> 30:43.762
somewhere a little
more private?

30:43.764 --> 30:46.499
Okay, maybe if you were
a petite cheerleader again.

30:46.501 --> 30:48.267
But I'm not sure
you fully realize this.

30:48.269 --> 30:49.434
You're a big,
threatening dude today,

30:49.436 --> 30:51.503
so, absolutely not.

30:51.505 --> 30:54.075
Right.
I get it.

30:55.876 --> 30:57.743
I don't know
if I have parents.

30:57.745 --> 30:58.810
Um...

30:58.812 --> 31:03.082
I assume so,
but I have no one to ask.

31:03.084 --> 31:06.184
So, every day of your life,
you've just woken up, and...

31:06.186 --> 31:09.454
Just tried to live that day
for that person.

31:09.456 --> 31:14.126
Not mess anything up for them,
make no mark, leave no trace.

31:14.128 --> 31:15.994
And you're never
that person again?

31:15.996 --> 31:18.798
No. I might see them
at school

31:18.800 --> 31:22.937
a week or a month later.
If I'm in the same area.

31:25.406 --> 31:28.274
So, like,
when you're somebody,

31:28.276 --> 31:30.943
are you them or still you?

31:30.945 --> 31:32.111
I'm me.

31:32.113 --> 31:35.381
You know, my consciousness,
my memories.

31:35.383 --> 31:37.383
But then I can also access

31:37.385 --> 31:39.218
their history
and their memories.

31:39.220 --> 31:41.621
But not all at once.

31:41.623 --> 31:44.024
The longer I'm in
someone that day,

31:44.026 --> 31:45.561
the more I know about them.

31:48.563 --> 31:49.961
Who else have you told this?

31:49.963 --> 31:52.932
I told you, no one else.

31:52.934 --> 31:54.970
That sounds really lonely.

31:57.638 --> 31:58.639
Can be.

31:59.473 --> 32:00.608
And sad.

32:02.511 --> 32:04.477
But it isn't

32:04.479 --> 32:08.482
because I've seen so much.

32:09.885 --> 32:13.118
I know what makes
each person different,

32:13.120 --> 32:15.020
and what makes everyone
the same, you know?

32:15.022 --> 32:17.757
I've seen the same
color blue

32:17.759 --> 32:21.128
look 50 different ways with
50 different pairs of eyes.

32:23.164 --> 32:24.297
But you never get to stay

32:24.299 --> 32:26.434
with anything long enough
to watch it grow.

32:28.435 --> 32:29.605
It's true.

32:31.306 --> 32:34.309
But I'd like to, though.

32:38.613 --> 32:40.180
If I show you something,

32:40.182 --> 32:42.084
will you promise
to show no one else?

32:45.153 --> 32:46.188
Check out my Instagram.

32:53.561 --> 32:56.496
I've posted pictures
any days that I could.

32:56.498 --> 33:00.266
Of people I've been,
and the things that I've seen.

33:00.268 --> 33:01.534
Of course it's a risk.

33:01.536 --> 33:03.469
I have to scrub
the login information

33:03.471 --> 33:05.503
every night
before I go to bed

33:05.505 --> 33:08.175
but it's good
to have a record.

33:15.116 --> 33:17.251
This still doesn't
prove anything.

33:18.520 --> 33:20.953
I mean, you could
just be getting these

33:20.955 --> 33:23.388
from other people
or the Internet.

33:23.390 --> 33:26.759
I could, but I'm not.
Wait, wait.

33:26.761 --> 33:28.763
Can we please meet again?

33:30.397 --> 33:33.301
I don't know. Yes, maybe.

33:35.103 --> 33:38.704
Just let me process this
for a little while, okay?

33:38.706 --> 33:40.038
Okay.

33:40.040 --> 33:41.510
Bye, A.

33:42.609 --> 33:44.212
Bye.

34:31.458 --> 34:32.893
Did you need me?

34:35.429 --> 34:36.431
No.

34:37.264 --> 34:38.367
I'm good.

35:05.093 --> 35:06.094
Hey!

35:08.463 --> 35:09.497
It's me.

35:10.564 --> 35:11.830
Remember?

35:11.832 --> 35:13.832
Yet another person
has the unique idea

35:13.834 --> 35:15.868
to prank me by pretending
to be the Devil.

35:15.870 --> 35:16.872
What?

35:19.006 --> 35:20.341
No, no.

35:22.243 --> 35:25.147
I'm hoping to write something
for my school newspaper.

35:28.348 --> 35:29.718
Actually, I do recognize you.

35:30.484 --> 35:31.486
You do?

35:33.421 --> 35:35.221
I'll meet with anyone
interested in the truth.

35:36.024 --> 35:37.723
Okay.

35:37.725 --> 35:39.859
See, he did something
to my memory

35:39.861 --> 35:41.963
so the whole night's
kind of hazy.

35:42.564 --> 35:43.665
But...

35:46.033 --> 35:48.169
I remember dancing.

35:48.970 --> 35:50.736
Then,

35:50.738 --> 35:53.508
I was in this unnaturally
tiny house.

35:54.408 --> 35:56.877
Then running for my life.

35:57.678 --> 35:59.044
Apparently, that evening,

35:59.046 --> 36:01.379
I told my mom that
he needed to borrow a car

36:01.381 --> 36:02.448
so I could go help
some friends

36:02.450 --> 36:04.549
write a musical about Jesus.

36:04.551 --> 36:06.720
And this should go
in your story.

36:07.388 --> 36:08.921
When he was within me

36:08.923 --> 36:11.225
he used my phone to access
his Instagram account.

36:13.727 --> 36:15.563
I was on Satan's social media.

36:16.863 --> 36:19.834
It was intense.

36:21.303 --> 36:23.401
It was a record
of all the other teenagers

36:23.403 --> 36:24.839
that he's taken over.

36:25.740 --> 36:27.473
Can I see?

36:27.475 --> 36:29.408
He kicked me off
and changed the password

36:29.410 --> 36:32.044
before I could save
any of the photos

36:32.046 --> 36:33.548
but I recognize you.

36:34.115 --> 36:35.548
What do you mean?

36:35.550 --> 36:38.084
From one of the photos.
In the aquarium.

36:38.086 --> 36:39.321
That was you.

36:41.321 --> 36:42.656
He possessed you, too,
didn't he?

36:43.790 --> 36:45.323
No.

36:45.325 --> 36:47.428
No, I wasn't possessed.

36:49.196 --> 36:54.133
When he was within you,
did he talk to you?

36:54.135 --> 36:55.567
I think that's
enough for today.

36:55.569 --> 36:57.336
Did you get a sense
of what he was like?

36:57.338 --> 36:59.471
Like, his personality?

36:59.473 --> 37:02.475
I know his personality.

37:02.477 --> 37:04.679
It's pure evil. He's Satan.

37:05.278 --> 37:06.514
Thank you.

37:13.354 --> 37:14.654
Justin, you cannot
threaten him!

37:14.656 --> 37:16.122
It's not a threat.

37:16.124 --> 37:17.455
I'm just gonna tell him,

37:17.457 --> 37:19.058
"Little dude, next time
you talk to my girlfriend

37:19.060 --> 37:20.125
I'mma help you out

37:20.127 --> 37:21.894
by beating the Devil
out of you."

37:21.896 --> 37:23.229
How is that a threat?

37:23.231 --> 37:24.696
Justin, that's the literal
definition of a threat.

37:24.698 --> 37:26.098
Rhiannon, tell him.

37:26.100 --> 37:28.600
Rhiannon, tell her.
No. Are you a dictionary?

37:28.602 --> 37:30.435
Are you a child?

37:30.437 --> 37:31.606
I'm not a child.

37:38.979 --> 37:39.981
Hey!

37:42.816 --> 37:44.452
How did you know it was me?

37:45.553 --> 37:47.955
Just the way you looked at me.

37:49.256 --> 37:50.990
Also, she doesn't go here.

37:50.992 --> 37:52.691
He doesn't go here.

37:52.693 --> 37:55.794
You're not very good
for his attendance record.

37:55.796 --> 37:58.430
I'm not good for anyone's
attendance record.

38:03.504 --> 38:04.539
Come on.

38:05.906 --> 38:07.071
Look, I thought you said

38:07.073 --> 38:08.439
you didn't wanna mess
anyone's life up.

38:08.441 --> 38:11.042
Speaking of which,
what happened to Nathan?

38:11.044 --> 38:12.377
I had to see you.

38:12.379 --> 38:15.480
I tried to get him home,
put him to bed

38:15.482 --> 38:18.216
but at 11:59, I pulled over
and passed out

38:18.218 --> 38:19.651
except I screwed up

38:19.653 --> 38:21.354
and forgot to erase
my Instagram info.

38:21.356 --> 38:22.453
He thinks you're the Devil.

38:23.557 --> 38:24.656
If I'm the Devil,

38:24.658 --> 38:26.158
humanity has nothing
to worry about.

38:26.160 --> 38:28.526
That's exactly what the Devil
would want humanity to think.

38:28.528 --> 38:32.730
I can't win with you
suspicious mortals, can I?

38:32.732 --> 38:35.870
Seriously,
why are you doing this?

38:36.771 --> 38:37.935
The day we met,

38:37.937 --> 38:40.740
I felt something
I've never felt before.

38:40.742 --> 38:42.510
And I don't wanna let that go.

38:44.611 --> 38:48.180
About that day,
how is it okay, what you did?

38:48.182 --> 38:50.549
I let you kiss me because
I thought you were Justin.

38:50.551 --> 38:52.517
I told you something
incredibly personal

38:52.519 --> 38:53.685
because I thought
you were Justin.

38:53.687 --> 38:55.020
He never would've understood.

38:55.022 --> 38:56.923
I was in his mind, Rhiannon.
I know him.

38:56.925 --> 38:58.256
Are you serious?

38:58.258 --> 39:00.558
I know him better than you do.
He is my boyfriend.

39:00.560 --> 39:01.894
You know you shouldn't
be with him.

39:01.896 --> 39:04.430
Who should I be with, then?
You?

39:04.432 --> 39:07.499
I mean, off the top
of my head, that's an option.

39:07.501 --> 39:08.700
This isn't funny, A.

39:08.702 --> 39:11.405
This is so weird.
I mean, today you're...

39:13.173 --> 39:16.709
Not everyone's body
aligns with their mind.

39:16.711 --> 39:19.944
But I'm not asking you to give
Vic a chance, Rhiannon,

39:19.946 --> 39:22.082
I'm asking you
to give me a chance.

39:34.294 --> 39:36.798
What do you remember
from that day at the beach?

39:38.566 --> 39:39.665
Um...

39:39.667 --> 39:40.902
That it was super good?

39:42.635 --> 39:46.540
I also remember this.

39:48.008 --> 39:49.910
Can I ask you something else?

39:51.479 --> 39:52.944
Yeah.

39:52.946 --> 39:55.383
What do you like about us?

39:57.618 --> 39:58.785
Us?

39:58.787 --> 40:00.922
Yeah, like, our connection.

40:03.390 --> 40:04.392
Uh...

40:05.392 --> 40:07.560
Um...

40:07.562 --> 40:10.595
We're so connected.
Because we're...

40:10.597 --> 40:12.232
We make a really great team.

40:15.435 --> 40:17.803
Like, we've always
got each other's backs,

40:17.805 --> 40:19.404
like, when you wouldn't
let me drive drunk

40:19.406 --> 40:20.571
the other night at Steve's.

40:20.573 --> 40:21.939
That was super clutch.

40:21.941 --> 40:26.111
And, I mean, that night
with that weird dude,

40:26.113 --> 40:28.180
it reminded me

40:28.182 --> 40:29.984
that I would fight like crazy
not to lose you.

40:30.685 --> 40:31.753
You know?

40:32.986 --> 40:36.223
'Cause our connection
is really powerful.

40:52.439 --> 40:54.205
Steve was so wasted
at the party.

40:54.207 --> 40:56.008
He's flirting with
this girl from Monroe

40:56.010 --> 40:58.209
and turns out that's
Stephanie's best friend.

41:13.493 --> 41:16.227
Jolene, can I have the car
when we get home?

41:16.229 --> 41:17.729
That's the shit I don't like.

41:17.731 --> 41:19.200
I have to hit the library.

41:19.700 --> 41:20.901
Nerd.

41:41.589 --> 41:42.787
Hey.

41:42.789 --> 41:44.490
I hope we still have
